dtPr><w:id w:val="-1089472405"/><w:placeholder><w:docPart w:val="DefaultPlaceholder_-1854013440"/></w:placeholder><w:showingPlcHdr/></w:sdtPr><w:sdtContent><w:p w14:paraId="0F3F7DDE" w14:textId="3F08860A" w:rsidR="00047099" w:rsidRPr="00047099" w:rsidRDefault="00047099" w:rsidP="00047099"><w:r w:rsidRPr="004C6807"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="PlaceholderText"/></w:rPr><w:t>Click or tap here to enter text.</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:sdtContent></w:sdt><w:p w14:paraId="724C0A9F" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00047099" w:rsidRPr="00047099" w:rsidRDefault="00047099" w:rsidP="00047099"><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00047099"><w:t>Reminder: A scene recreation starts with the reality of the space you will stand in.</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00047099"><w:br/><w:t>Nothing should be imagined that cannot be filmed.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3917D3E4" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00047099" w:rsidRDefault="00047099"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:eastAsiaTheme="majorEastAsia" w:cstheme="majorBidi"/><w:color w:val="0F4761" w:themeColor="accent1" w:themeShade="BF"/><w:sz w:val="28"/><w:szCs w:val="28"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="594E8D06" w14:textId="7D4E1F68" w:rsidR="00047099" w:rsidRDefault="00047099" w:rsidP="00047099"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading3"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00047099"><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t>SECTION 2. CREATE A LOGLINE THAT FITS THOSE LIMITS</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7F251996" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00347D10" w:rsidRPr="00347D10" w:rsidRDefault="00347D10" w:rsidP="00347D10"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t xml:space="preserve">A logline condenses the essential action of the moment into a single, clear sentence. It identifies who the character is in this beat, what they are trying to do, and what stands in their way. Like a thematic statement or a clear line of conflict in a screenplay, the logline gives shape to both the explicit action the viewer will </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramStart"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>see</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramEnd"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t xml:space="preserve"> and the implicit meaning suggested by how that action unfolds.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4D53885A" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00347D10" w:rsidRPr="00347D10" w:rsidRDefault="00347D10" w:rsidP="00347D10"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t xml:space="preserve">A useful logline for a short moment or recreated scene focuses on what can be filmed: an observable goal, a concrete obstacle, and the tension created when the two meet. It should guide the choices you will make with blocking, framing, and composition. If the moment is too internal or relies on information the camera cannot show, the </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramStart"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>logline</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramEnd"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t xml:space="preserve"> needs to be simplified until the action is readable on screen.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="18A2BE16" w14:textId="5400E2C4" w:rsidR="00347D10" w:rsidRPr="00347D10" w:rsidRDefault="00347D10" w:rsidP="00347D10"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t xml:space="preserve">Write your </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramStart"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>logline</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramEnd"/><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t xml:space="preserve"> below:</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:br/></w:r><w:sdt><w:sdtPr><w:id w:val="401178709"/><w:placeholder><w:docPart w:val="DefaultPlaceholder_-1854013440"/></w:placeholder><w:showingPlcHdr/><w:text/></w:sdtPr><w:sdtContent><w:r w:rsidRPr="004C6807"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="PlaceholderText"/></w:rPr><w:t>Click or tap here to enter text.</w:t></w:r></w:sdtContent></w:sdt></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="36632038" w14:textId="5CD31DA0" w:rsidR="00347D10" w:rsidRPr="00347D10" w:rsidRDefault="00347D10" w:rsidP="00347D10"><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>Before moving on, confirm that the logline:</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:br/></w:r><w:sdt><w:sdtPr><w:id w:val="-7526545"/><w14:checkbox><w14:checked w14:val="0"/><w14:checkedState w14:val="2612" w14:font="MS Gothic"/><w14:uncheckedState w14:val="2610" w14:font="MS Gothic"/></w14:checkbox></w:sdtPr><w:sdtContent><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Gothic" w:eastAsia="MS Gothic" w:hAnsi="MS Gothic" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t>☐</w:t></w:r></w:sdtContent></w:sdt><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>can be staged in the location you identified</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:br/></w:r><w:sdt><w:sdtPr><w:id w:val="-1794742964"/><w14:checkbox><w14:checked w14:val="0"/><w14:checkedState w14:val="2612" w14:font="MS Gothic"/><w14:uncheckedState w14:val="2610" w14:font="MS Gothic"/></w14:checkbox></w:sdtPr><w:sdtContent><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Gothic" w:eastAsia="MS Gothic" w:hAnsi="MS Gothic" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t>☐</w:t></w:r></w:sdtContent></w:sdt><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>expresses emotion through action rather than explanation</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:br/></w:r><w:sdt><w:sdtPr><w:id w:val="-1838215735"/><w14:checkbox><w14:checked w14:val="0"/><w14:checkedState w14:val="2612" w14:font="MS Gothic"/><w14:uncheckedState w14:val="2610" w14:font="MS Gothic"/></w14:checkbox></w:sdtPr><w:sdtContent><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Gothic" w:eastAsia="MS Gothic" w:hAnsi="MS Gothic" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t>☐</w:t></w:r></w:sdtContent></w:sdt><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>defines a conflict that can be shown visually</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:br/></w:r><w:sdt><w:sdtPr><w:id w:val="-399524270"/><w14:checkbox><w14:checked w14:val="0"/><w14:checkedState w14:val="2612" w14:font="MS Gothic"/><w14:uncheckedState w14:val="2610" w14:font="MS Gothic"/></w14:checkbox></w:sdtPr><w:sdtContent><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="MS Gothic" w:eastAsia="MS Gothic" w:hAnsi="MS Gothic" w:hint="eastAsia"/></w:rPr><w:t>☐</w:t></w:r></w:sdtContent></w:sdt><w:r w:rsidRPr="00347D10"><w:t>fits within a single beat rather than a full arc</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4A12B60A" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00047099" w:rsidRDefault="00047099"><w:r><w:br w:type="page"/></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7E87F807" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00047099" w:rsidRDefault="00047099" w:rsidP="00047099"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading3"/></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00047099"><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t>SECTION 3. WRITE ONLY WHAT THE CAMERA CAN SHOW</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="1F1A6C70" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="001E0005" w:rsidRPr="001E0005" w:rsidRDefault="001E0005" w:rsidP="001E0005"><w:r w:rsidRPr="001E0005"><w:t>This step converts your logline into the specific actions the camera will capture.</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="001E0005"><w:br/><w:t>These actions become the basis for your storyboard in the next section.</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="001E0005"><w:br/><w:t>If you cannot list them clearly here, you will not be able to draw or shoot the scene.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="53BED42F" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="001E0005" w:rsidRPr="001E0005" w:rsidRDefault="001E0005" w:rsidP="001E0005"><w:r w:rsidRPr="001E0005"><w:t>List the key actions in the order they occur.</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="001E0005"><w:br/><w:t>Each action should be physical, observable, and tied to the conflict in your logline.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5ADF048F" w14:textId="52F5DCE8" w:rsidR="001E0005" w:rsidRPr="001E0005" w:rsidRDefault="001E0005" w:rsidP="001E0005"><w:r w:rsidRPr="001E0005"><w:t>Action 1 (the moment begins when…):</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="001E0005"><w:br/></w:r><w:sdt><w:sdtPr><w:id w:val="-1308621998"/><w:placeholder><w:docPart w:val="DefaultPlaceholder_-1854013440"/></w:placeholder><w:showingPlcHdr/><w:text/></w:sdtPr><w:sdtContent><w:r w:rsidRPr="004C6807"><w:rPr><w:rStyle w:val="PlaceholderText"/></w:rPr><w:t>Click or tap here to enter text.</w:t></w:r></w:sdtContent></w:sdt></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="38BEDAF6" w14:textId="6E3D5D1C" w:rsidR="001E0005"